when is a good age to leave your dog out of its crate during the day i have an month old puppy who is house trained he is crated during the day while i'm at work when is a good age to leave them out alone he does tend to chew on things there is no set age for when to start leaving your pet without crating it all depends on how much you can trust him to not potty in the house or chew something up if you think he might be ready you can start slow by just leaving him for minutes while you do some yard work or something if that goes well then increase it to minutes and so on since he's still chewing on things you may want to wait a few more months Housebreaking Dog training Crate training Fancy rat Labrador Retriever Dog Domestic rabbit Battle of the Bulge Puppy mill Havanese Beethoven (film) Dog agility Greyhound racing Tooth Socialization Social rule Chew Valley Lake Cocaine Hobo German Shepherd Dog USS Chew (DD-106) Balto (film) Weight training USS Tunny (SS-282) Nintendogs Tobacco smoking Paget's disease of bone Halitosis The Sims Docking Elimination communication Shaggy dog story Hamster Getting Things Done Korea Jindo Dog Pet Sounds Traumatic incident reduction Topps Ultima Online Unclean animals Quake III Arena Dairy Sake 2005 Iditarod Natural Selection (computer game) Crash Team Racing 101 Dalmatians: The Series English Springer Spaniel Rugrats Apollo 8 Firefly (television series) Crash Bandicoot Shetland Sheepdog USS Uhlmann (DD-687) Quill (film) USS Wilkes (DD-441) The Fairly OddParents Lisa the Vegetarian Drag racing Grand Theft Auto (game) Tobacco USS Whale (SS-239) Big Ben Compact audio cassette Golden Retriever Tooth enamel Sick Puppy Marathon (sport) Mixed-breed dog Elephant USS Atule (SS-403) Mojave people Parachuting Gerald Durrell Midfielder Current teachings of Prem Rawat Explosive material USS Ajax (AR-6) American Eskimo Dog Obedience training Majin Buu Saga Magic (illusion) Garfield Clifford's Puppy Days Day USS Sea Dog (SS-401) Battle of the Somme 